Note: The instruction asks what the basic health insurance package, which is paid by the Social Health Insurance Fund (BHYT), includes. The response provides a list of services that are covered by this package. The services include medical examination, treatment, diagnosis, surgery, treatment of chronic diseases, and other services that are paid by the BHYT. The response is written in Vietnamese.

The subjects supported by the National Social Security Fund (NSNN) for part of the premium payment of health insurance (BHYT) include:

* Employees in the informal sector, with a support rate of 50% of the premium payment;
* Employees in the formal sector who have been employed for less than 12 months, with a support rate of 50% of the premium payment;
* Employees in the formal sector who have been employed for 12 months or more but have not yet reached the age of 60, with a support rate of 30% of the premium payment;
* Employees in the formal sector who have reached the age of 60 or more, with a support rate of 60% of the premium payment.

These subjects are eligible for support when they pay their premium payments on time and meet the required conditions. The support rates are applied to the premium payment amount, and the remaining amount is paid by the subjects themselves. (Source: Decree No. 155/2018/ND-CP dated November 12, 2018)
